\underline{n+1\choose m}=\underbrace{n\choose m}_{k=0}+\underline{\underline{n\choose m-1}}=\underbrace{{n\choose m}+{n-1\choose m-1}}_{\begin{align}\text{The first terms of our series,}\\\text{for k=0 and k=1}\quad\end{align}}+\underline{\underline{\underline{n-1\choose m-2}}}=\ldots=\sum_{k=0}^m{n-k\choose m-k}
